libsha1
------------------------------------------
libsha1 is a tiny library providing SHA1 implementation, created for
facilitating X server compilation on devices when larger libraries containing
SHA1 implementations (OpenSSL, Mozilla NSS) are not needed.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.34-6
  libsha1-devel-0.3-1bl1
  libsha1_0-0.3-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-2
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/dottedmag/libsha1

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/dottedmag/libsha1/archive/0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsha1-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsha1-0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsha1-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsha1-0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsha1_0-0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsha1-devel-0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsha1)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsha1.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsha1/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libsha1/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libsha1/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libsha1/README

(libsha1_0)
  /usr/bin/cygsha1-0.dll

(libsha1-devel)
  /usr/include/libsha1.h
  /usr/lib/libsha1.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsha1.pc

